### GET Server Health
GET http://localhost:5000/
Content-Type: application/json

### GET All Content Data (Public)
# This will fetch the content straight from your newly attached MongoDB!
GET http://localhost:5000/api/content
Content-Type: application/json

### POST Admin Login (Required for updating content)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "kiosk2026"
}

### PUT Update Content (Protected)
# This will update the MongoDB database with the new payload.
# If your VSCode REST Client doesn't auto-resolve variables, paste the token from the login response below.
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/content
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "localeInfo": {
    "locale": "PAYATAS B (UPDATED VIA MONGODB)",
